subSubSection.paragraph:
Male postabdomen: Sternite 5 longer than wide, somewhat ovoid, posterior margin notched, with a thin, short anterior apodeme (
Fig. 193
). Surstylus subrectangular distally, somewhat scooped. Postgonite with very broad anterior lobe, thin and strongly curved posterior lobe. Basiphallus somewhat swollen, no distinct epiphallus, preepiphallus very short. Distiphallus with a thin spinose dorsal tube flanked by paired spike-like sclerites (
Fig. 190
).
